==English==
===Etymology===
Variant of [[hallo]]
====Note====
This variant of [[hallo]] is sometimes falsely credited to [[w:Thomas Edison|Thomas Edison]], or to one of his employees, as a coinage (or as a variant of [[w:Hungarian language|Hungarian]] [[hallom]]) for telephone use.  However Edison in fact favoured "[[ahoy]]!" and '''hello''' pre-dates the invention of the telephone by over 300 years.

